  <dashboards>
    <dashboard name='Story 1' type='storyboard'>
      <layout-options>
        <title>
          <formatted-text>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>FINANCIAL MARKET INSIGHTS: A MULTI-VIEW STORY</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Æ </run>
          </formatted-text>
        </title>
      </layout-options>
      <style>
        <style-rule element='story-point-caption'>
          <format attr='width' value='353' />
        </style-rule>
      </style>
      <size maxheight='764' maxwidth='1016' minheight='764' minwidth='1016' sizing-mode='fixed' />
      <zones>
        <zone h='100000' id='2' type-v2='layout-basic' w='100000' x='0' y='0'>
          <zone h='97906' id='11' param='vert' removable='false' type-v2='layout-flow' w='98426' x='787' y='1047'>
            <zone h='5105' id='12' type-v2='title' w='98426' x='787' y='1047'>
              <zone-style>
                <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                <format attr='margin' value='4' />
              </zone-style>
            </zone>
            <zone h='92801' id='7' param='vert' removable='false' type-v2='layout-flow' w='98426' x='787' y='6152'>
              <zone h='92801' id='1' param='vert' removable='false' type-v2='layout-flow' w='98426' x='787' y='6152'>
                <zone fixed-size='160' h='20942' id='4' is-fixed='true' paired-zone-id='5' removable='false' type-v2='flipboard-nav' w='98426' x='787' y='6152' />
                <zone h='71859' id='5' paired-zone-id='4' removable='false' type-v2='flipboard' w='98426' x='787' y='27094'>
                  <flipboard active-id='2' nav-type='caption' show-nav-arrows='true'>
                    <story-points>
                      <story-point caption='HISTORICAL STOCK OF THE SELECTED COMPANIES          &#10;&#10;What do these historical stock price trends tell us about the financial market’s evolution, and how can we use these insights to guide our strategic decisions?' captured-sheet='AAPL Time Series' id='1'>
                        <capturedDeltas>
                          <worksheet name='AAPL Time Series'>
                            <style delta-type='added'>
                              <style-rule element='table'>
                                <format attr='show-null-value-warning' value='false' />
                              </style-rule>
                            </style>
                          </worksheet>
                        </capturedDeltas>
                      </story-point>
                      <story-point caption='STOCK PERFORMANCE TROUGH CENTRAL TENDENCY&#10;&#10;What do these measures of central tendency reveal about the typical performance of the selected companies, and how can we leverage this insight for more informed financial decisions?' captured-sheet='Central Tendency' id='2' />
                      <story-point caption='STOCK PRICE DISTRIBUTION WITH BOX PLOT&#10;&#10;THE Box plot reveal the distribution and volatility of the selected companies’ stock prices, and how can we use these insights for more strategic financial decisions?' captured-sheet='Boxplot' id='3' />
                      <story-point caption='DISTRIBUTION OF THE SELECTED COMPANIES&#10;&#10;What does the size of each circle reveal about the distribution of these companies stock metrics, and how can we apply this knowledge to make more informed financial decisions?' captured-sheet='DISTRIBUTION' id='4' />
                      <story-point caption='VOLUME TRENDS &amp; PERCENT DIFFERENCES&#10;&#10;Which days see the biggest swings in volume, and how does this align with price changes?' captured-sheet='Sheet 7' id='5'>
                        <capturedDeltas>
                          <worksheet name='Sheet 7'>
                            <filter class='categorical' column='[federated.13w1jaa09dfykb155di401t0d4re].[md:Date:ok]'>
                              <groupfilter function='member' level='[md:Date:ok]' member='20211123' user:ui-domain='database' user:ui-enumeration='inclusive' user:ui-marker='enumerate' />
                            </filter>
                          </worksheet>
                        </capturedDeltas>
                      </story-point>
                    </story-points>
                  </flipboard>
                </zone>
              </zone>
            </zone>
          </zone>
          <zone-style>
            <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
            <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
            <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
            <format attr='margin' value='8' />
          </zone-style>
        </zone>
        <zone flipboard-zone-id='5' forceUpdate='true' h='26702' id='9' story-point-id='2' type-v2='text' w='33268' x='3445' y='56152'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>By looking at the average stock prices, we gain a snapshot of how these companies perform over our selected time frame. This helps us spot patterns, understand the market sentiment, and make strategic choices for our monitoring tool</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
        <zone flipboard-zone-id='5' forceUpdate='true' h='28272' id='13' story-point-id='2' type-v2='text' w='33268' x='58366' y='55105'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run bold='true' fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000'>High average</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000'> stock prices often indicate strong market valuation and investor confidence, suggesting potential for continued growth.</run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000'>Low average</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000'> stock prices may reflect undervaluation, lower investor sentiment, or the need for strategic shifts to boost market performance. </run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
        <zone flipboard-zone-id='5' h='17670' hidden='true' id='14' story-point-id='3' type-v2='text' w='33268' x='56004' y='34162'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run bold='true' fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000'>Box Plot Components</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000'>: The box shows the middle 50% of values, the line in the box is the median, and the whiskers/dots can indicate outliers or extreme price points. </run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
        <zone flipboard-zone-id='5' h='35340' hidden='true' id='15' story-point-id='3' type-v2='text' w='33268' x='56201' y='54188'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run bold='true' fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000'>Wider vs Narrower Spread</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000'>: A wider spread suggests higher volatility, while a narrower spread indicates more consistent performance.</run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000'>Higher vs Lower Median</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000'>: A higher median may suggest stronger market valuation, whereas a lower median might indicate undervaluation or potential opportunities for growth. </run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
        <zone flipboard-zone-id='5' forceUpdate='true' h='18063' hidden='true' id='16' story-point-id='4' type-v2='text' w='33268' x='64469' y='79188'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run bold='true' fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontsize='10'>Larger Circles</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontsize='10'>:  Signify higher values, indicating greater market presence or performance.</run>
            <run fontalignment='0'>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontsize='10'>Smaller Circles</run>
            <run fontalignment='0' fontcolor='#000000' fontsize='10'>: Represent lower values, suggesting potential undervaluation, growth opportunities, or different risk profiles. </run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
      </zones>
      <simple-id uuid='{7CFA4A74-98A9-4960-9CA5-D50F63F5F43F}' />
    </dashboard>
  </dashboards>
